Step 1: Identify the needed components.
• The Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio is typically computed as:
  Main Business Revenue / Average Accounts Receivable.
• From the balance sheet, the Accounts Receivable at the start of the period is 0.00 (2023-12-31) and the end of the period is 2,923,459.19 (2024-01-31). Thus, the average Accounts Receivable = (0 + 2,923,459.19) / 2 = 1,461,729.60 (approximately).
• From the income statement, the Main Business Revenue for the period is given as 6,920,513.79.

Step 2: Calculate the Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio.
  Ratio = Main Business Revenue / Average Accounts Receivable
    = 6,920,513.79 / 1,461,729.60
    ≈ 4.73

Step 3: Present the result in the required JSON format.

{
  "solution": {"Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio": "4.73"}
}
